From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: VyOS LS1046A maintainers <dpaa1@vyos-ls1046a-build>
Date: Tue, 10 Jun 2026 14:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] system offload classify - HW exact-match flow steering CLI
 (M3-3b production consumer)

Adds the production CLI consumer for the FMan PCD Coarse-Classifier
flow-steering path (spec sec 5.4):

  set system offload classify interface <ethN> rule <1-32> protocol (tcp|udp)
  set system offload classify interface <ethN> rule <1-32> source address <a.b.c.d>
  set system offload classify interface <ethN> rule <1-32> source port <1-65535>
  set system offload classify interface <ethN> rule <1-32> destination address <a.b.c.d>
  set system offload classify interface <ethN> rule <1-32> destination port <1-65535>
  set system offload classify interface <ethN> rule <1-32> queue <0-127>

The conf_mode script shells out to the NIC-neutral standard interface -
ethtool ntuple (`ethtool -N <intf> flow-type ... action <queue> loc
<rule-1>`) - mirroring the vyos-1x-025 ingress-policer pattern (CLI ->
standard kernel tool -> driver bridge). On the LS1046A Mono Gateway the
dpaa driver's rxnfc bridge (board patch 0109) rebuilds the port's FMan
CC static tree on every rule mutation: matching flows are
silicon-steered to the chosen RX frame queue (and thereby its servicing
CPU) before the kernel RX path ever runs. On hardware without the
capability ethtool fails with "Operation not supported" and commit
aborts loudly - no silent no-op.

Apply model: every commit flushes the ntuple rules of all interfaces
present in either the old (effective) or new config (parse `ethtool -n`
Filter: lines, delete each), then re-inserts the new rule set sorted by
rule number; rule number is the match priority (lower wins, mapped to
ethtool location rule-1). A hardware reject mid-commit rolls back every
rule installed by that commit.

Documented hardware limitation (also enforced nowhere - both spellings
are accepted): the FMan KeyGen-extracted compare key carries no L4
protocol byte, so a tcp and a udp rule with identical addresses/ports
steer the SAME traffic on LS1046A.

Purely additive: two new files (interface definition XML + conf_mode
script), no upstream file is touched, so this patch is immune to
upstream context drift. XML validated against
schema/interface_definition.rng (RelaxNG: valid); script passes
python3 -m py_compile.

Signed-off-by: VyOS LS1046A maintainers <dpaa1@vyos-ls1046a-build>
Rev 2 (2026-06-10): dropped unused `from vyos.utils.process import cmd`
 (pylint W0611 fails the vyos-1x Makefile gate; CI run 27304735703).

---
diff --git a/interface-definitions/system_offload.xml.in b/interface-definitions/system_offload.xml.in
new file mode 100644
index 000000000..37f98d338
--- /dev/null
+++ b/interface-definitions/system_offload.xml.in
@@ -0,0 +1,127 @@
+<?xml version="1.0"?>
+<interfaceDefinition>
+  <node name="system">
+    <children>
+      <node name="offload" owner="${vyos_conf_scripts_dir}/system_offload.py">
+        <properties>
+          <help>Hardware flow offload</help>
+          <priority>385</priority>
+        </properties>
+        <children>
+          <node name="classify">
+            <properties>
+              <help>Hardware exact-match ingress flow steering (NIC flow classifier)</help>
+            </properties>
+            <children>
+              <tagNode name="interface">
+                <properties>
+                  <help>Ingress interface to classify on</help>
+                  <completionHelp>
+                    <script>${vyos_completion_dir}/list_interfaces --type ethernet</script>
+                  </completionHelp>
+                  <valueHelp>
+                    <format>txt</format>
+                    <description>Ethernet interface name</description>
+                  </valueHelp>
+                  <constraint>
+                    #include <include/constraint/interface-name.xml.i>
+                  </constraint>
+                </properties>
+                <children>
+                  <tagNode name="rule">
+                    <properties>
+                      <help>Classification rule (lower numbers match first)</help>
+                      <valueHelp>
+                        <format>u32:1-32</format>
+                        <description>Rule number (lower number = higher match priority)</description>
+                      </valueHelp>
+                      <constraint>
+                        <validator name="numeric" argument="--range 1-32"/>
+                      </constraint>
+                      <constraintErrorMessage>Rule number must be in range 1 to 32</constraintErrorMessage>
+                    </properties>
+                    <children>
+                      <leafNode name="protocol">
+                        <properties>
+                          <help>Transport protocol of the flow</help>
+                          <completionHelp>
+                            <list>tcp udp</list>
+                          </completionHelp>
+                          <valueHelp>
+                            <format>tcp</format>
+                            <description>Transmission Control Protocol</description>
+                          </valueHelp>
+                          <valueHelp>
+                            <format>udp</format>
+                            <description>User Datagram Protocol</description>
+                          </valueHelp>
+                          <constraint>
+                            <regex>(tcp|udp)</regex>
+                          </constraint>
+                          <constraintErrorMessage>Protocol must be tcp or udp</constraintErrorMessage>
+                        </properties>
+                      </leafNode>
+                      <node name="source">
+                        <properties>
+                          <help>Source match criteria</help>
+                        </properties>
+                        <children>
+                          <leafNode name="address">
+                            <properties>
+                              <help>Source IPv4 address (exact match)</help>
+                              <valueHelp>
+                                <format>ipv4</format>
+                                <description>IPv4 source address</description>
+                              </valueHelp>
+                              <constraint>
+                                <validator name="ipv4-address"/>
+                              </constraint>
+                            </properties>
+                          </leafNode>
+                          #include <include/port-number.xml.i>
+                        </children>
+                      </node>
+                      <node name="destination">
+                        <properties>
+                          <help>Destination match criteria</help>
+                        </properties>
+                        <children>
+                          <leafNode name="address">
+                            <properties>
+                              <help>Destination IPv4 address (exact match)</help>
+                              <valueHelp>
+                                <format>ipv4</format>
+                                <description>IPv4 destination address</description>
+                              </valueHelp>
+                              <constraint>
+                                <validator name="ipv4-address"/>
+                              </constraint>
+                            </properties>
+                          </leafNode>
+                          #include <include/port-number.xml.i>
+                        </children>
+                      </node>
+                      <leafNode name="queue">
+                        <properties>
+                          <help>Hardware RX queue to steer matching flows to</help>
+                          <valueHelp>
+                            <format>u32:0-127</format>
+                            <description>RX queue index (determines servicing CPU)</description>
+                          </valueHelp>
+                          <constraint>
+                            <validator name="numeric" argument="--range 0-127"/>
+                          </constraint>
+                          <constraintErrorMessage>Queue must be in range 0 to 127</constraintErrorMessage>
+                        </properties>
+                      </leafNode>
+                    </children>
+                  </tagNode>
+                </children>
+              </tagNode>
+            </children>
+          </node>
+        </children>
+      </node>
+    </children>
+  </node>
+</interfaceDefinition>
diff --git a/src/conf_mode/system_offload.py b/src/conf_mode/system_offload.py
new file mode 100755
index 000000000..0657515ea
--- /dev/null
+++ b/src/conf_mode/system_offload.py
@@ -0,0 +1,153 @@
+#!/usr/bin/env python3
+#
+# Copyright VyOS maintainers and contributors <maintainers@vyos.io>
+#
+# This program is free software; you can redistribute it and/or modify
+# it under the terms of the GNU General Public License version 2 or later as
+# published by the Free Software Foundation.
+#
+# This program is distributed in the hope that it will be useful,
+# but WITHOUT ANY WARRANTY; without even the implied warranty of
+# MERCHANTABILITY or FITNESS FOR A PARTICULAR PURPOSE. See the
+# GNU General Public License for more details.
+#
+# You should have received a copy of the GNU General Public License
+# along with this program.  If not, see <http://www.gnu.org/licenses/>.
+#
+# system offload classify - hardware exact-match ingress flow steering.
+#
+# Drives the NIC's standard ethtool ntuple (rxnfc) interface:
+#
+#   ethtool -N <intf> flow-type (tcp4|udp4) [src-ip A] [dst-ip B]
+#           [src-port P] [dst-port Q] action <queue> loc <rule-1>
+#
+# On the LS1046A Mono Gateway the dpaa driver bridges these rules into an
+# FMan PCD Coarse-Classifier static tree (board patches 0098/0106/0108/0109):
+# a matching flow is silicon-steered to the chosen RX frame queue (and
+# thereby its servicing CPU) before the kernel ever sees the frame. On
+# hardware without the capability ethtool fails with "Operation not
+# supported" and commit aborts loudly.
+#
+# NOTE (documented hardware limitation): the FMan KeyGen-extracted compare
+# key carries no L4 protocol byte, so a tcp and a udp rule with identical
+# addresses/ports steer the SAME traffic on LS1046A.
+
+import re
+
+from sys import exit
+
+from vyos.config import Config
+from vyos.utils.process import rc_cmd
+from vyos import ConfigError
+from vyos import airbag
+airbag.enable()
+
+def get_config(config=None):
+    if config:
+        conf = config
+    else:
+        conf = Config()
+    base = ['system', 'offload']
+
+    offload = conf.get_config_dict(base, key_mangling=('-', '_'),
+                                   get_first_key=True,
+                                   no_tag_node_value_mangle=True)
+
+    # Interfaces that carried rules in the previous (effective) config must
+    # be flushed even when they vanish from the new config.
+    effective = conf.get_config_dict(base, key_mangling=('-', '_'),
+                                     get_first_key=True,
+                                     no_tag_node_value_mangle=True,
+                                     effective=True)
+
+    old_ifaces = set(effective.get('classify', {}).get('interface', {}))
+    new_ifaces = set(offload.get('classify', {}).get('interface', {}))
+    offload['flush_interfaces'] = sorted(old_ifaces | new_ifaces)
+
+    return offload
+
+def verify(offload):
+    if not offload or 'classify' not in offload:
+        return None
+
+    for iface, iface_cfg in offload['classify'].get('interface', {}).items():
+        rules = iface_cfg.get('rule', {})
+        if not rules:
+            raise ConfigError(f'classify interface "{iface}" has no rules')
+        for num, rule in rules.items():
+            prefix = f'classify interface "{iface}" rule {num}'
+            if 'protocol' not in rule:
+                raise ConfigError(f'{prefix}: protocol is required')
+            if 'queue' not in rule:
+                raise ConfigError(f'{prefix}: queue is required')
+            has_match = False
+            for side in ('source', 'destination'):
+                side_cfg = rule.get(side, {})
+                if 'address' in side_cfg or 'port' in side_cfg:
+                    has_match = True
+            if not has_match:
+                raise ConfigError(
+                    f'{prefix}: at least one source/destination '
+                    'address or port is required')
+    return None
+
+def generate(offload):
+    return None
+
+def _flush_ntuple(iface):
+    """Delete every installed ntuple rule on @iface (best-effort)."""
+    rc, out = rc_cmd(f'ethtool -n {iface}')
+    if rc != 0:
+        return
+    for loc in re.findall(r'^Filter:\s+(\d+)', out, re.MULTILINE):
+        rc_cmd(f'ethtool -N {iface} delete {loc}')
+
+def apply(offload):
+    if not offload:
+        return None
+
+    for iface in offload.get('flush_interfaces', []):
+        _flush_ntuple(iface)
+
+    if 'classify' not in offload:
+        return None
+
+    for iface, iface_cfg in offload['classify'].get('interface', {}).items():
+        for num in sorted(iface_cfg.get('rule', {}), key=int):
+            rule = iface_cfg['rule'][num]
+            flow_type = 'tcp4' if rule['protocol'] == 'tcp' else 'udp4'
+            opts = f'flow-type {flow_type}'
+            src = rule.get('source', {})
+            dst = rule.get('destination', {})
+            if 'address' in src:
+                opts += f' src-ip {src["address"]}'
+            if 'port' in src:
+                opts += f' src-port {src["port"]}'
+            if 'address' in dst:
+                opts += f' dst-ip {dst["address"]}'
+            if 'port' in dst:
+                opts += f' dst-port {dst["port"]}'
+            # rule number is 1-based match priority; ethtool location is
+            # 0-based, lowest location matches first.
+            loc = int(num) - 1
+            rc, out = rc_cmd(f'ethtool -N {iface} {opts} '
+                             f'action {rule["queue"]} loc {loc}')
+            if rc != 0:
+                # Roll back anything we already installed on this commit.
+                for flushed in offload.get('flush_interfaces', []):
+                    _flush_ntuple(flushed)
+                raise ConfigError(
+                    f'classify interface "{iface}" rule {num}: hardware '
+                    f'rejected the rule: {out.strip()} (hardware flow '
+                    'steering unavailable on this platform?)')
+    return None
+
+if __name__ == '__main__':
+    try:
+        c = get_config()
+        verify(c)
+        generate(c)
+        apply(c)
+    except ConfigError as e:
+        print(e)
+        exit(1)
